<header class="hero">
  <div class="content">
    <h1>Bone Conduction Headphones & Bone Conduction Earphones in India – Open Ear Sound by NG EarSafe</h1><br>
    <!-- <button class="cta">Learn More</button> -->
<p>Bone conduction technology is fascinating! Instead of sending sound through your ear canal like regular headphones, it actually delivers sound through the bones in your skull. So, when you wear bone conduction headphones, they rest on your cheekbones and use vibrations to send the sound directly to your inner ear. The great thing is it completely bypasses your eardrum, so your ear canal stays open. This means you can still hear what’s going on around you, which is awesome for things like outdoor workouts or commuting where you need to stay aware of your surroundings.</p>    
  </div>
</header>

<section>
  <div class="grid-flex">
    <div class="col col-image" style="background-image: url('https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0804/5762/9975/files/Final.gif?v=1709019972');">
    </div>
    <div class="col col-text">
      <div class="Aligner-item">
        <p>Instead of traditional headphones that plug your ears, bone conduction headphones, sometimes also called “bonephones” or bone conduction earphones, transmit sound waves directly through the bones in your skull, bypassing your eardrums entirely, allowing users to listen to device audio while keeping their ears free—making it the safest technology to listen to audio. This benefits people who want to protect their ears from damage in the long run, have a conductive hearing disability, or need to stay aware of their surroundings.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

